This paper deals with the algorithmic theory of Markov decision processes, which falls under the category of game theory (cs.GT). The paper also introduces a new algorithm based on the sweep-line technique from computational geometry, which falls under the category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The paper also involves the analysis of previous algorithms, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper deals with timed games, which falls under the category of control systems (cs.SY).
